  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p>\n<p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p>\n<p>Skim through these steps</p>\n<p>Wash your fruit and veg</p>\n<p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 mins)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-ham-hock-ploughmans-and-chutney-dressing/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now let's get started!</strong></p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Tear up the <strong>ciabatta<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces, then add to a baking tray with the <strong>walnuts</strong> and a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>black pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Put the tray into the oven for 6-8 min or until crisp – these are your <strong>croutons and toasted walnuts</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-ham-hock-ploughmans-and-chutney-dressing/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-low heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>shredded</strong> <strong>ham hock</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until warmed through </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-ham-hock-ploughmans-and-chutney-dressing/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the shredded ham hock is in the pan, halve the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-ham-hock-ploughmans-and-chutney-dressing/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the<strong> apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters, then carefully remove the cores</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>apple quarters</strong> (skin on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-ham-hock-ploughmans-and-chutney-dressing/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Using a peeler, create shavings of the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: Grate any leftover cheese and sprinkle this onto the salad at the end!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-ham-hock-ploughmans-and-chutney-dressing/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>green tomato chutney</strong>,<strong> cider vinegar</strong> and <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> to a small bowl</p>\n<p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> chutney dressing</strong> </p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-ham-hock-ploughmans-and-chutney-dressing/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Assemble your salad by dividing the <strong>lamb's lettuce</strong>, <strong>halved tomatoes</strong> and <strong>chopped apples</strong> between your bowls</p>\n<p>Sprinkle over the<strong> shredded</strong> <strong>ham hock</strong>,<strong> croutons</strong> and<strong> toasted walnuts </strong>and drizzle over the <strong>chutney dressing</strong></p>\n<p>Top with the <strong>cheddar shavings </strong>and any<strong> remaining grated cheese</strong> and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
